The paper deals with the problem of maximizing aggregate user utilities over a multi-hop network, subject to link capacity constraints, maximum end-to-end delay constraints, and user throughput requirements. This problem is important for supporting real-time multimedia traffic, which suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. However, the paper also deals with network optimization and algorithm design, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. The paper also considers the concave function of the achieved throughput or the experienced maximum delay, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. Additionally, the paper considers the problem of simultaneously considering maximum delay constraints and throughput requirements, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a polynomial-time approximation algorithm named PASS, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
